<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-15T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-15T23:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./2:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-16T12:00:00+08:00">October 16,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 16—5:55
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>907. Hankow’s October 14, 5 p.m. The Legation is telegraphing Adams to
                            take this matter up at once with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs with a
                            view to effecting the release of the Reverend Nelson at the earliest
                            possible moment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>